latestPosts.caption:
5 Spring Wardrobe essentials that we don’t need to buy. 🤍

Moving into a new season, there’s so many new bits online everywhere! It can be so tempting to buy new, before I consider buying new I  work with what I already have. These are 5 staples most of us probably already own. These are pieces I rework every year. Mix and match with classic and trend pieces to make them feel fresh. 

1. The crisp white tee - I prefer a slightly oversized fit. You can pick up some great quality white t shirts, that wash well, keep their shape from the highstreet. My go to places to shop are @arketofficial & @cosstores 
2. The denim jacket - oversized denim or a closer fit. I own both and wear both differently. My most worn is my oversized denim jacket.
3. The white Jean - not just for Spring, I wear mine all year round, but in Spring knitwear & a thong sandal ( in particular) is my fav way to wear them
4. The oversized white shirt - a decent white shirt takes some research. I look for a structured fit, oversized and not too long ( as I am 5ft 2) you can find the best white shirts at @withnothingunderneath 
5. The leather jacket - I own so many different styles & have worn leather jackets since my early teens, they are really a part of my personality. My most worn & favs come from @allsaints @thisiswhistles @toteme @desavarylondon I’ve tagged the leathers I’m wearing on the phone on this post. 

#fashioninspo #springwardrobe #whattowearnow #whatshot #springfashıon #springinspo #springtrends
